[
    {
        "content": "<p>This was briefly discussed in <a href=\"#narrow/stream/253118-theory.3A-categorical-probability/topic/Does.20the.20category.20of.20standard.20Borel.20spaces.20have.20pullbacks.3F\">a previous thread</a> but I don't think this particular question got answered (and the more I try to follow up the points raised there the less confident I am in my understanding). So I'm wondering if anyone knows the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Does <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{BorelStoch}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">BorelStoch</span></span></span></span></span> (or its deterministic subcategory) have finite coproducts?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Does it have countable coproducts? (I'm guessing it doesn't have uncountable ones)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Are the coproducts \"what they should be\", i.e. can we think of a map into <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A+B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> as first flipping a biased coin to choose <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span> or <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> and then choosing an element of the appropriate space?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Does the tensor distribute over the coproducts?</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>(I think that if the category of standard Borel spaces and measurable maps has coproducts then these will also be coproducts in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{BorelStoch}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">BorelStoch</span></span></span></span></span>, although if I'm wrong I'm happy to be corrrected.)</p>",
        "id": 407069713,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1702215566
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At least countable coproducts are there, and they are the disjoint union of (standard Borel) measurable spaces. <br>\n(Since left-adjoints preserve coproducts.)</p>",
        "id": 407070465,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Perrone",
        "timestamp": 1702216185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sorry, but what's the definition of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf{BorelStoch}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbf\">BorelStoch</span></span></span></span></span>?</p>",
        "id": 407071548,
        "sender_full_name": "Todd Trimble",
        "timestamp": 1702216929
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Equivalently, either the category of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_Borel_space\">standard Borel spaces</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markov_kernel\">Markov kernels</a>, or the Kleisli category of the <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/monads+of+probability%2C+measures%2C+and+valuations\">Giry monad</a> on standard Borel spaces.</p>",
        "id": 407071748,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Perrone",
        "timestamp": 1702217040
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275989\">Paolo Perrone</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/253118-theory.3A-categorical-probability/topic/Coproducts.20in.20BorelStoch/near/407070465\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>At least countable coproducts are there, and they are the disjoint union of (standard Borel) measurable spaces. <br>\n(Since left-adjoints preserve coproducts.)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>what's the left adjoint you're referring to here?</p>",
        "id": 407071954,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1702217170
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276071\">Nathaniel Virgo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/253118-theory.3A-categorical-probability/topic/Coproducts.20in.20BorelStoch/near/407071954\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275989\">Paolo Perrone</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/253118-theory.3A-categorical-probability/topic/Coproducts.20in.20BorelStoch/near/407070465\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>At least countable coproducts are there, and they are the disjoint union of (standard Borel) measurable spaces. <br>\n(Since left-adjoints preserve coproducts.)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>what's the left adjoint you're referring to here?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The inclusion functor from measurable maps to Markov kernels.</p>",
        "id": 407072332,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Perrone",
        "timestamp": 1702217452
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was just going to say, based on the Kleisli description: for any Kleisli category on a monad <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M: C \\to C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span>, the forgetful functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Kleisli}(M) \\to C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Kleisli</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> has a left adjoint.</p>",
        "id": 407074089,
        "sender_full_name": "Todd Trimble",
        "timestamp": 1702218772
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, yes the tensor does distribute over the coproducts (i.e. <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/distributive+monoidal+category\">distributive monoidal category</a>). This is because it does in standard Borel spaces (e.g. this is part of <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1908.10510\">Ruiyuan Chen's characterization of standard Borel spaces</a>). </p>\n<p>Not sure that \"distributive Markov categories\" have been used before, but we used them in the paper I mentioned recently (see <a href=\"https://www.cs.ox.ac.uk/people/samuel.staton/popl24.pdf\">page 8</a>).</p>",
        "id": 407088539,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Staton",
        "timestamp": 1702229165
    }
]